.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-ARTIFACTS" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.20" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-artifacts \- Export tracked artifact bundles after a run
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose artifacts [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Export tracked artifact bundles collected under the tracked job directory into the configured export directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read. Default: compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to export instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--bundle\fR \fINAME\fR
Artifact bundle name to export; may be passed multiple times.
.TP
\fB--tarball\fR
Also create tar.gz archives for exported bundles.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose artifacts \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose artifacts \-f compose.yaml \-\-bundle checkpoints \-\-tarball
hpc\-compose artifacts \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
